First Lady Dr. Jill Biden visited Rhode Island and delivered a speech at Providence College, expressing her passion for teaching and the importance of educators. She shared her personal journey of initially wanting to pursue a career in fashion marketing but finding her true calling in teaching after volunteering with adults who couldn't read. Dr. Biden emphasized that teaching is not just a job, but a calling to shape the world one student at a time. She also highlighted the need for more teachers across the country and encouraged listeners to consider a career in education. Dr. Biden praised President Joe Biden's commitment to supporting educators and outlined his efforts in recruiting, respecting, and retaining teachers. She urged aspiring teachers to imagine the impact they could have on students' lives and emphasized the joy and fulfillment that comes with being an educator. Dr. Biden concluded by inviting listeners to join the cause and change the world together, one student at a time.